This is how I do it for an ID that is a UUID, but still select and show username not UUID, so my Comment.CreatedBy is a UUID, but I only show the user "usernames". Note I use the to string FN to convert for the actual value displayed.
```
<MudSelect Label="@_L["lbl_CreatedBy"]"  T="string" 
							OffsetY="true" Dense="true"
							ToStringFunc="@UserNameConverter"
							MultiSelection="false"
							@bind-SelectedValue="Comment.CreatedBy">
						@foreach (var usr in UserList.Items)
						{
							<MudSelectItem T="string" Value="@usr.ID">@usr.UserName</MudSelectItem>
						}
```

```
UserNameConverter = (userID) =>
			{
				return (from u in UserList.Items
						where u.ID == userID
						select u).First().UserName;
			};
```

